# Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows two distinct structures:

## Structure 1 (Left Side - Vehicle):
- This structure resembles a vehicle with:
  - 2 orange cylindrical blocks as wheels
  - 1 yellow rectangular block with curved top (half-cylinder) on top of the wheels
  - 1 blue cube on top of the yellow block

## Structure 2 (Right Side - House/Robot):
- This structure has:
  - 1 blue cube in the center
  - 4 orange triangular/wedge blocks surrounding the blue cube
  - 1 green rectangular block on top

## Block Count and Layers:
- Total blocks used: 10 blocks
- Structure 1 has 4 blocks and 3 layers
- Structure 2 has 6 blocks and 3 layers

# Selected Blocks from the Dictionary

For Structure 1 (Vehicle):
- 1 blue cube (index 1)
- 1 yellow half-cylinder (index 10)
- 1 yellow rectangular block (index 6)
- 2 orange cylindrical blocks (index 9)

For Structure 2 (House/Robot):
- 1 blue cube (index 1)
- 1 green rectangular block (index 4)
- 4 orange triangular blocks (indices 12, 13, 15, 16)

# Assembly Order

```
{
  Step1: Move block with index 9
  Step2: Move block with index 9
  Step3: Move block with index 6
  Step4: Move block with index 10
  Step5: Move block with index 1
  Step6: Move block with index 1
  Step7: Move block with index 12
  Step8: Move block with index 13
  Step9: Move block with index 15
  Step10: Move block with index 16
  Step11: Move block with index 4
}
```

The assembly process first builds the vehicle structure (steps 1-5) by placing the wheels, then the rectangular base, the half-cylinder, and topped with the blue cube. Then it constructs the house/robot structure (steps 6-11) by placing the central blue cube, surrounding it with four triangular blocks, and finally placing the green rectangular block on top.
